Treasure chest space
Released18 October 2006 (Update)
MembersYes
QuestNo
LocationPlayer-owned house (costume room)
OptionsBuild
ExamineStores your precious belongings.
Advanced data
Object ID18813

The treasure chest space is a hotspot in the costume room of a player-owned house that is only visible to the player when in building mode. Flatpacked versions of the furniture can be used to upgrade this space instead of raw materials.

Uses[edit | edit source]

A full list of items that can be stored in a treasure chest can be found below.

Item Use
Oak treasure chest Store beginner and easy Treasure Trails rewards.
Teak treasure chest Store beginner, easy and medium Treasure Trails rewards.
Mahogany treasure chest Store all levels of Treasure Trails rewards.

  1. ^ Press this key on your keyboard while in the Creation Menu to build this item.

Storable rewards

Item sets from the Grand Exchange cannot be stored in a treasure chest, even if all of the components can be stored within the Treasure chest.

This list contains all items that can be stored in treasure chests of any tier.

Not storeable[edit | edit source]

  • Gnomish firelighters (including the Gnomish firelighter)
  • God pages
  • Purple sweets
  • Master scroll book
  • Ornament kits
  • Items that can be found elsewhere, such as food or runes

Changes[edit | edit source]

Date Changes
16 September 2020
(update)

3rd age sets have been split apart into individual pieces.

2 September 2020
(update | poll)

Treasure chests can store partially completed sets.

23 July 2020
(update)

Furniture inside the costume room now follow an upgrading build pattern, similar to furniture found in the workshop. The toy box excluded from this change.

28 April 2016
(update)

The spelling of Monocle has been corrected for player-owned house treasure chests.

8 October 2015
(update)

Fixed a typo on the player-owned house Treasure chest interface.
